description:
Inscriptions include the following:
1) On leaf 4 below the title “Green Bean Casserole” is handwritten in ink “Serves 4.” A typed recipe follows and at the bottom of page is printed by hand, “The pepper and onion all disappear.”
2) On leaf 6 is a handwritten recipe for rice with a note at the bottom “good with shrimp or ham”.
3) On leaf 7 is a handwritten recipe for “Baked Eggplant Slices”.
4) On leaf 8 is a handwritten recipe for “Mushrooms and Zucchini”; 
5) At top of leaf 13 is handwritten “Katherine Ann / Porter” above “Onion Pie”, which is a typed recipe.
6) On leaves 19 and 20 is a handwritten recipe for “Fresh Spinach Salad”; 
7) On leaf 21 is a handwritten recipe entitled “For better garlic bread”;
8) On leaf 22 is a handwritten recipe for “Slaw”;
9) On leaf 30 is a handwritten recipe for “Cheese & Onion” with “to try” at top viewer’s right corner; and
10) On about leaf 36 or maybe later is “1904 Doody (getting house ready) / (I made it plain I wanted the [undecipherable] “The people down here / do not as a rule do things / by storm’ / (He ended up doing it [undecipherable], at night after work.)”

The following inserts are in the journal, except where noted:
1) Inserted between leaves number 12 and 13 is blank unused envelope with “EUDORA WELTY / 1119 PINEHURST STREET / JACKSON, MISSISSIPPI 39202” on the back flap*;
2) Between leaves number 25 and 26 is a handwritten recipe for “Poppy Seed Dressing”;
3) Between leaves number 26 and 27 is a newspaper clipping with no date, no name of paper, and no publisher and at top of which is handwritten “Fruit Salad” in all caps;
4) Between leaves 27 and 28 is a recipe card for “CHICKEN WITH CHESTNUTS AND HAM” copyright Williams-Sonoma 1982; 
5) Between 30 and 31 is a printed recipe for “Frothy Vegetable Soup” which was torn from a magazine, the name of which is not on the clipping; and
6) Between 33 and 34 is a clipping from “Morning, February 7, 1973”, The Times-Picayune, “Hints from Heloise / French Bread Recipe / by Heloise Cruse / ((c) 1973, King Features Synd.). Note: Black leather 6-ring binder journal containing typed and handwritten recipes presumably created or recorded by Eudora Welty.
